# Gateway & Codex integration

## Services

- `GatewayServer` — HTTP routing on `127.0.0.1:8765`, third-party model proxy, OpenAI pass-through.
- `LoopbackHTTPServer` — Network.framework HTTP server, SSE support.
- `Translator` — Responses ↔ Chat Completions translation, namespace tool mapping, think-block stripping.
- `ModelCatalog` — `~/.codexgateway/custom_model_catalog.json` + `providers.json`.
- `CodexConfig` — managed blocks in `~/.codex/config.toml` (markers `# >>> codexgateway managed >>>`). `requires_openai_auth` on the `codexgateway` provider is derived from `isSignedIn()` (auth.json): `false` when signed out so Codex skips login for local-only Ollama/custom use; `true` when signed in for native GPT/ChatGPT pass-through. Legacy `codexbar` blocks are rewritten to `codexgateway` on refresh/patch. Automatic callers (startup, auth watcher, restart) use `refreshManagedConfigIfApplied()` — they only re-patch when the block already exists, never injecting into a native Codex. Explicit apply is `patchCodexConfig()` via `SettingsStore.updateGatewayConfig` / add-model/provider actions.
- `CodexAuthWatcher` — watches `~/.codex` for sign-in changes and re-patches config automatically; `restartCodexDesktop()` also re-patches before relaunch.
- `CodexAppServer` — locate Codex binary, restart Codex Desktop.

## Config paths

- `Paths.modelCatalog`, `Paths.providersConfig`, `Paths.codexConfig`, `Paths.codexAuth`
- Gateway: `Paths.gatewayHost`:`Paths.gatewayPort` (default `127.0.0.1:8765`)

## After changing these services

Run `make test` and update `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `README.md` (if user-visible), and this rule or `codexgateway-gateway` skill when integration contracts change.

## Do not

- Duplicate HTTP routing logic outside `GatewayServer`.
- Write to `~/.codex/config.toml` outside `CodexConfig` managed blocks without good reason.
- Re-enable WebSocket/voice endpoints without explicit user request.
